node.text:
Please watch this before you hire a moving company!!! 

On June 17th, 2021, we were moved out of our home in Idaho and were forced to pay our moving company more than triple the quoted amount. Today, we have paid them over $80K, and are still missing more than $40K worth of belongings. 

They have stopped answering our calls and texts and we have hired lawyers. But we are sharing this story so others can be wiser and more educated about the moving industry than we were. There were many red flags along the way that we didn't know to look for. And many moments that we were so panicked and stressed and vulnerable where we were taken advantage of and forced to pay cash and even more money. 

Our hope is that this message, although ongoing and embarrassing for us, will help protect others making major moves and life changes from predators in the moving industry.

node.text: We put together a little montage video of renovating our modern cottage over the last two years and it makes me tear up seeing where we started and how far we’ve come. I see that there are so many memories—really happy memories here. Living in a construction zone is not easy, but to me it was all worth it and even meant to be. #cljmoderncottage

node.title: 2 years of renovating our modern cottage

Manually searching for promo codes is a thing of the past—Honey is free to install and just takes two clicks. node.text: Salad doesn’t always feel “wintery” to me, but once the holidays pass and my body can’t take anymore sugar, I just need something fresh. But I also like to eat seasonally, when I can. This Winter Salad features a lot of vegetables (root and otherwise), shaved super thin, and dressed in a sweet potato dressing with mild hint of curry. Full recipe at chrislovesjulia.com. #chriscooks #salad #dairyfree #grainfree #glutenfree #healthyeating

node.text:
Just setting the Fall scene over here. To me, the main ingredient to any gathering is lighting. We populated our patio with lots of accent lighting from @loweshomeimprovement — in the trees and the bushes and the fountain — and basked in all of the glowy ambiance. With our new string lights overhead and cozy torches burning all around us, we couldn’t resist having a family s’mores night. We lit the fire pit and got to toasting marshmallows and — thanks to all of our new outdoor lighting — told stories late into the night. 

Make sure to head over to @loweshomeimprovement IG and use their Project Matchmaker story to make your family gathering extra special this fall!
#FallTogether #LowesPartner
